This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with word embeddings, which are widely used in Natural Language Processing. Additionally, the paper proposes a new model that learns word and sense embeddings jointly, which is a common topic in the CL community. 

The paper also involves the use of large corpora and knowledge from semantic networks, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval), as these fields often involve the use of large datasets and knowledge-based approaches. 

Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed method in a variety of tasks, which could indicate that it belongs to the sub-category cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), as this field often involves the evaluation of models in real-world scenarios.
